[{"id":"VH899617","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><include href=\"../Passage/VH899609.qti.xml\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\"></include></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which of the structures in the diagram is the site where the nuclear power plant accidents at Three Mile Island and Chernobyl occurred?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH899617_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<div class=\"stimulus_reference\" xmlns=\"http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/apip/apipv1p0/qtiitem/imsqti_v2p2\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a diagram of a nuclear power plant. There are 4 areas of the diagram labeled with the letters A, B, C, and D. Â The flow of water and steam through the nuclear power plant is as follows. A containment structure surrounds an object labeled, A, that contains control rods and a reactor. Water is moved in a clockwise fashion through the structure that contains the control rods and reactor, and then through a steam generator in an endless cycle. A steam line moves from the steam generator into a structure labeled B. A pump moves water from the structure labeled B back into the generator, and that flow continues in an endless cycle. A structure labeled D moves water from an external reservoir into a condenser, which is below the structure labeled B, and then into the tower labeled C. Water from the tower labeled C can also flow back into the condenser, and arrows at the top of the tower labeled C indicate that omissions are passed into the atmosphere.\" height=\"360\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH899609.g06.png\" width=\"525\" /></div>\n</div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">A</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">B</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">C</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">D</p>"],"answer":0}]